<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by taobob on 08-31-2000 06:12 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">A ranger who can't make his own arrows from time to time is a complete waste of time IMHO. Also, who's gonna make that Trueshot longbow for you to use?? Or did you want to actually pay someone else to actually make it for you...

As far as camping for items and experience, I think that everyone has done this from time to time, but the main problem arises when people COMPETE for the same camping spot. 

This is where the problems lie in camping, is that people would rather be selfish and take the camp (or the experience and loot that come with it) for themselves rather than sharing. This can be especially frustrating when it is a high level who is farming items from enemies that they don't get exp for. I can't tell you how many times I have hunted wisps (for exp and loot)to find the occasional Level 20 character killing wisps simply because they are in financial difficulties. 

The solution to this that I always apply is to let the selfish person have at the camp, wish them luck while secretly cursing them to a speedy death at the hand of a creature that is more of a challange to them. 

I also have my own little trick to play on them which I advise all Rogues (and classes that have invisibility available to them) to give a try... First make a quick disappearing act then Do an */emote ruffles through your pocket.*, followed immediately by */emote steals 10pp and 7gp from you!!*... hehehe   :)  Most of the time they get so furious that they will run off looking for you... leaving the camp unattended (even the high levels fall for this  :) ) I have them  on hot buttons to so that they go off fast... This is sometimes too fun...

Blackivar ruffles through your pocket..
Blackivar steals 9pp and 6gp from you!!
 :)



------------------
Blackivar the Cunning
Halfling Rogue
15th Season
Druzzil Ro Server</TEXTAREA>
